3.  No person shall establish or maintain any of the following private
healthcare facilities or services without approval being granted under
paragraph 12(a) or operate or provide any of such facilities or
services without a licence granted under paragraph 19(a):
(a) a private hospital;
(b) a private psychiatric hospital;
18                                    Laws of Malaysia                          ACT 586
(c) a private ambulatory care centre;
(d) a private nursing home;
(e) a private psychiatric nursing home;
(f) a private maternity home;
(g) a private blood bank;
(h) a private haemodialysis centre;
(i) a private hospice;
(j) a private community mental health centre;
(k) any other private healthcare facility or service or health-
related service as the Minister may specify, from time to
time, by notification in the Gazette; and
(l) a private healthcare premises incorporating any two or more
of the facilities or services in paragraphs (a) to (k).
